field.value:
The current implementations of Castle.MonoRail.Framework.Helpers.AbstractHelper.RenderScriptBlockToSource  make the assumption that the current URL has an extension, e.g. the simpler of the two overloads:

		protected string RenderScriptBlockToSource(string url)
		{
			return string.Format("<script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"{0}.{1}?" + MonoRailVersion + "\"></script>",
				context.ApplicationPath + url, context.UrlInfo.Extension);

		}
[see dot between {0} and {1}]

I am using MonoRail with extension-less URLs (like "http://localhost/MyProject/Home/Index"). When I e.g. use FormsHelper.InstallScripts, the generated URL contains a dot, like:
<script type="text/javascript" src="/MonoRail/Files/FormHelperScript.?RC3_0006"></script> [see dot before ?]

I attached a patch for the problem (no unit test for it, though).
